    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-02T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-02T13:00:00-05:00" n="377"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 763.72113/639</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MEV1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-02T15:00:00-03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 2, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 3, 8.53 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister of Finance confirmed to me today current report that Brazilian
                    Government is taking over and liquidating the three German banks as well as the
                    principal German houses in Brazil with capital and offices in Germany. Please
                    telegraph <hi rend="italic">résumé</hi> of manner in which German houses in the
                    United States are treated whose capital and offices are wholly located in the
                    United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MEV1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
